                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72111W74/7</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-21">
                        <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 22, 6:50 a.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>446. Your August 7, 8 p.m., and my August 20, 425.<note n="1" xml:id="d1137fn1"
                        >Latter not printed.</note> Foreign Office informs me that British
                    Government have no hesitation in giving you every assurance that they will
                    respect the neutrality of Liberia. They rely on the Government of the Republic
                    to take all proper steps to protect their neutrality in any circumstances which
                    may arise.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
